			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is a thread in the pet section, but this section gets more action, and I was wondering if you are noticing a difference in our pets Hit/Miss ratio.  I did no parsing, I was close enough to see both hits and misses at all times, and all I really have is observation from memory.
<br />

<br />
My senario was LoY boat Dandilak (sp?).  59 magician with 57 Earth pet BO3 and DS (Air pet wasnt even lasting through a fight on Lt blue cons).  Pet was rarely hitting for max or even close to max damage and missing what seemed like 50% of the time (Sorry I havent used any parsers).  Typically on the boat Dandy, 57 earth pet would rarely go below 50% health on Lt blue mobs, but last night he was typically under 20% after the fight (usually 1 Shock of steel thrown in).  I am sure without Shock of steel the pet would not have survived the fight.  Low db mobs would require two shocks and pet would be under 20% and many time under 10% health.
<br />

<br />
It could just have been a bad night, or maybe I just didnt realize how much our pets actually miss on mobs that are DB to it.  It was a bit disheartning.  But, if that is the way it is I will just turn off the pet hits/miss and live with it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
